li.p:
Next, we check the input value p. We have the following.

	    p\amp \stackrel{T_{a,b}}{\longrightarrow} p
	    p\amp \stackrel{s^{-1}}{\longrightarrow}
	      \frac{(\im(b),-\re(b),\im(a))}{\sqrt{1-(\re(a))^2}} 
	    \amp \stackrel{h}{\longrightarrow}
	      \frac{(\im(a),\re(b),\im(b))}{\sqrt{1-(\re(a))^2}}
	    \amp \stackrel{R_{r_{a,b}}}{\longrightarrow} \frac{(\im(a),\re(b),\im(b))}{\sqrt{1-(\re(a))^2}}
	    \amp
	      \stackrel{h}{\longrightarrow}\frac{(\im(b),-\re(b),\im(a))}{\sqrt{1-(\re(a))^2}}
	    \amp \stackrel{s}{\longrightarrow} p

	  Next, we check the input value 0. We have the
	  following.

	    0\amp \stackrel{T_{a,b}}{\longrightarrow}
	      \frac{b}{a^\ast}

	    0\amp \stackrel{s^{-1}}{\longrightarrow}
	      (0,0,-1)

	    \amp \stackrel{h}{\longrightarrow}
	      (-1,0,0)

	    \amp \stackrel{R_{r_{a,b}}}{\longrightarrow}
	      (|b|^2 - |a|^2,-2\im(ab),2\re(ab)) \;\;(\text{use  } r(-i)r^\ast)

	    \amp \stackrel{h}{\longrightarrow}
	      (2\re(ab),2\im(ab),|b|^2-|a|^2)

	    \amp \stackrel{s}{\longrightarrow} \frac{b}{a^\ast}


	  Finally, we check the input value \infty. We have the
	  following.

	    \infty\amp \stackrel{T_{a,b}}{\longrightarrow}
	      -\frac{a}{b^\ast}

	    \infty\amp \stackrel{s^{-1}}{\longrightarrow}
	      (0,0,1)

	    \amp \stackrel{h}{\longrightarrow}
	      (1,0,0)

	    \amp \stackrel{R_{r_{a,b}}}{\longrightarrow}
	      (-|b|^2 + |a|^2,2\im(ab),-2\re(ab)) \;\;(\text{use  } rir^\ast)

	    \amp \stackrel{h}{\longrightarrow}
	      (-2\re(ab),-2\im(ab),|a|^2-|b|^2)

	    \amp \stackrel{s}{\longrightarrow} -\frac{a}{b^\ast}

ol.li:
For , assume the set up in
	the suggestion. Using , we have

	  \cosh(c) \amp=  \frac{1+u^2}{1-u^2} 
	  \amp = \frac{1+\left|\frac{B-A}{1-A^\ast B}\right|^2}{1-\left|\frac{B-A}{1-A^\ast B}\right|^2}

	  \amp = \frac{1+\frac{|A|^2+|B|^2}{1+|A|^2|B|^2}}{1-\frac{|A|^2+|B|^2}{1+|A|^2|B|^2}}

	  \amp = \frac{1+|A|^2 + |B|^2 + |A|^2|B|^2}{1-|A|^2 -
	    |B|^2 + |A|^2|B|^2}
	  \amp = \frac{(1+|A|^2)(1 + |B|^2)}{(1-|A|^2)(1- |B|^2)}

	  \amp =  \cosh(a)\cosh(b).

      For , assume the set up in
	the suggestion. Using , we have

	  \cos(c) \amp=  \frac{1-u^2}{1+u^2} 
	  \amp = \frac{1-\left|\frac{B-A}{1+A^\ast B}\right|^2}{1+\left|\frac{B-A}{1+A^\ast B}\right|^2}

	  \amp = \frac{1-\frac{|A|^2+|B|^2}{1+|A|^2|B|^2}}{1+\frac{|A|^2+|B|^2}{1+|A|^2|B|^2}}

	  \amp = \frac{1-|A|^2 - |B|^2 + |A|^2|B|^2}{1+|A|^2 +
	    |B|^2 + |A|^2|B|^2}
	  \amp = \frac{(1-|A|^2)(1 - |B|^2)}{(1+|A|^2)(1+ |B|^2)}

	  \amp =  \cos(a)\cos(b).
